boolean

operators

- vals: 'True' and 'False'
- any obj can be tested for its truth value
- falsy values (convert to 'False'): False, 0, None, empty string/list/dict/tuple/set/range
    - truthy values: all other vals
- operators
    - and: logical AND
    - or: logical OR
    - ==/!=: compare vals
    - is (not): compare identity
        - only useful in conjunction with None
        - id(obj) returns unique identity of given obj (built-in func)
    - in (not): check containment, e.g. char in string
    - &=/|=: boolean combined with assignment
- multiple comparisons in one line possible (chaining)

EXAMPLE
a, b, c = 3, 3, 3
print(a is b and a is c)# True

a, b, c = 1, 2, 3
print(a < b < c)        # True

res = False
res &= True  # False
res |= True  # True
